Clean, Transform, and Load Data with Data Prep

Data Prep provides a visual interface in CRM Analytics that allows you to build recipes that prepare data and load it into a target. Use the graph of a recipe to see where the data comes from and how it flows through the recipe to the target.

A recipe consists of nodes. You can add different types of nodes to bring in, manipulate, and write data to a target. The graph shows inputs, appends, aggregates, filters, joins, and output, as well as transforms that change raw data.

Select a Transform node to see its transformations in the Details area. Preview the results of each transformation step in the Preview tab. When you run a recipe, CRM Analytics applies the function of each node on the input data, and then outputs the results to the specified target.

Data Prep Access Based on Your User Type

Not all Data Prep users need access to all data prep features. To support advanced and limited user types, CRM Analytics comes with two user permissions: Edit Analytics Dataflows and Edit Dataset Recipes.

Create a Recipe with Data Prep

Use a Data Prep recipe to clean, transform, and enrich data before loading it into one or more targets. Preview the results as you build it. Run the saved recipe to write the results to the targets.

Preview Results in a Data Prep Recipe

Catch mistakes early by reviewing the results of each node and transformation that you add to a Data Prep recipe.

Profile Columns to Understand Data in a Data Prep Recipe

Run column profiling on sample data to estimate key stats about columns. Column profiles are available only for columns shown in preview.

Limitations When Using Data Prep

Consider the following limitations before building recipes:
* A graph doesn't show every transformation.
* Transform nodes can have multiple steps.
* Node details and preview tabs provide more information than the graph.
* Running a recipe applies functions to input data and outputs results to targets.
title: Clean and Transform Data with Data Prep
